Question 5: Triangle Type Checker
Write a Python program that takes three sides of a triangle as input and determines:
•	If all three sides are equal, print "Equilateral Triangle."
•	If any two sides are equal, print "Isosceles Triangle."
•	If all three sides are different, print "Scalene Triangle."
•	If the sum of any two sides is not greater than the third side, print "Not a valid triangle."
________________________________________
Question 6: ATM Cash Withdrawal
Write a Python program that asks the user for the amount to withdraw. The program should check:
•	If the amount is a multiple of 100, proceed further.
o	If the amount is greater than 5000, print "Daily limit exceeded."
o	Else, print "Transaction successful."
•	If the amount is not a multiple of 100, print "Invalid amount. Enter multiples of 100."
