Question 7: Vehicle Speed Checker
Write a Python program that takes the speed of a vehicle as input and prints the following:
•	If speed is below 60 km/h, print "Safe speed."
•	If speed is between 60 and 100 km/h, print "Drive carefully."
•	If speed is above 100 km/h, check:
o	If speed is above 120 km/h, print "Overspeeding! Heavy fine imposed."
o	Else, print "Warning! Reduce your speed."
